  + [purpose] is classify finite Lambda overlay candidates by global stability, near-reference stability, and drift-in/drift-out behavior
  + [not_purpose] is new scans, new windows, denser offsets, proof, disproof, RH evidence, zero certification, critical-line authority, primary zero detection, or identity fusion
  + [proof_status] is finite_cross_window_cutoff_stability_class_not_rh_evidence

& [MeasuredComparison] is existing_stability_row_synthesis
  + [global_cutoff_rows] are cutoff_stability_rows from existing Lambda window/cutoff trace
  + [global_cross_window_rows] are cross_window_rows from existing Lambda window/cutoff trace
  + [near_reference_rule] is endpoints are within 0.5 t units of the same reference label
  + [source_near_rule] is the source endpoint is within 0.5 t units of a reference label
  + [drift_rule] is source-near endpoint matched to a target outside the same near-reference pocket
  + [reference_labels] are first_zero_ordinate_reference, second_zero_ordinate_reference, and third_zero_ordinate_reference as labels only
  + [allowed_output] is analysis pass and focal-point update only

  = must: use existing stability rows only
  = must: report global stability separately from near-reference pocket stability
  = must: report cutoff stability and cross-window stability separately
  = must: report whether near-reference instability is local instability or drift across the comparison
  = must: decide whether the overlay branch should pause
  = must: preserve proof_status finite_cross_window_cutoff_stability_class_not_rh_evidence
  - never: claim stable near-reference pockets are zeros, RH evidence, proof, disproof, or a central identity
  - never: authorize denser scans from stability alone

& [CrossWindowCutoffStabilityClassSJS] is the specification justification trace
  + [processed_stage_set] is source_preserved, delineated, canonicalized, constraint_checked, justified, and synthesis_scoped
  + [processing_result] is accepted_bounded_stability_class_contract
  + [reasoning_result] is the existing Lambda stability rows are sufficient to separate dense heat, stable pockets, and drift without adding another computation grid

(cross_window_cutoff_stability_class) :finite Lambda stability-class synthesis: /global stability, near-reference pockets, drift, pause decision/ |RH evidence|
  + [inside] is bounded synthesis of existing cutoff and window stability rows
  + [boundary] is orientation and branch restraint
  |outside| proof, disproof, zero certification, critical-line authority, new scans, exact-reference dominance, and single-surface identity
